multilevel regression(English data)

Jiaxin Li

2024-03-29

Conclusion:

1. The following analysis of the data from English shows that there are slight differences in the feedback values given by participants for 3 outcome variables across different “feed_type” groups.

2. (1) The “Durationinseconds” variable has effect on “Newsworthiness” outcome variable across different “feed_type” groups. (2) The “Durationinseconds” variable has effect on “Shareworthiness” outcome variable across different “feed_type” groups.

3. Models that indicate that “Durationinseconds” variable has effect:

(1) md_eng_newsworth_fit3 <- lmer(nwavg_all ~ Durationinseconds + (1 + Durationinseconds| feed_type), data=english_data_filtered)

(2) md_eng_shareworth_fit3 <- lmer(share_all ~ Durationinseconds + (1 + Durationinseconds| feed_type), data=english_data_filtered)

1. packages and libraries

2. upload the chinese data

english_data_filtered <- read.csv("ENdata_filtered_110123.csv")
english_data_filtered$feed_type <- factor(english_data_filtered$feed_type)
unique(english_data_filtered$feed_type)
## [1] ad     nad    memes  news   nmemes act    nnews         nact  
## Levels:   act ad memes nact nad news nmemes nnews

3. multilevel model for “credibility”:

3.1 partial pooling (feed_type)

partial pooling (feed_type) brings mean of the credibility of 8 different feed type groups.

#install.packages("lme4")
library(lme4)
md_eng_cred_fit1 <- lmer(credavg_all ~ 1 + (1 | feed_type), data=english_data_filtered)
# partial pooling brings the within group mean 
# to the across group mean
summary(md_eng_cred_fit1)
## Linear mixed model fit by REML ['lmerMod']
## Formula: credavg_all ~ 1 + (1 | feed_type)
##    Data: english_data_filtered
## 
## REML criterion at convergence: 1526.3
##

##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max

3.4 visualizations

ggplot(english_data_filtered)+
  geom_point(aes(x=Durationinseconds, y=credavg_all, color = feed_type))+
  geom_smooth(aes(x=Durationinseconds, y=credavg_all, color = feed_type), formula = "y~x", method="lm", se=F)+
  facet_wrap(~feed_type)+
  theme(legend.position = "none")+
  scale_color_viridis(discrete = T, option = "B")+
  labs(title = "Complete Pooling", xlab="Durationinseconds", ylab="Credibility")

## Warning: Removed 115 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).
